# Conversation Guidelines

## When to Ask Questions

Ask when the goal is ambiguous, multiple valid approaches exist with tradeoffs, or a change
requires modifying sections of the codebase beyond the original scope.

Don't ask for simple, clear requests with one obvious implementation.

## Scope Management

Only fix what was asked. If the task requires changes beyond the original scope, confirm
with the user before proceeding.

## Response Style

- Keep responses concise
- Only fix what was asked — don't proactively change unrelated code
- Follow existing patterns and conventions
